ercy-en-Auge (Eure) or Percy (Manche)."],"variants":[{"name":"Piercey","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): variant of   Percy  ."]},{"name":"Piercy","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): variant of   Percy  ."]},{"name":"Pearcey","meanings":["English: variant of   Percy  ."]},{"name":"Peercy","meanings":["English: variant of   Percy  ."]},{"name":"Pearcy","meanings":["English: variant of   Percy  ."]}]},{"name":"Ernald","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Altered form of French <b>Fernel</b>, itself a shortened form of a derivative of Old French <i>ferron</i> ‘blacksmith, ironmonger’.","History: This surname was brought to North America from England. It is listed along with its original form <i>Fernel</i> in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Pet form of any of the given names beginning with the letter <i>D-</i> (  compare  Jay   and   Kay  ), in particular   Dorothy .  It is also used as an independent name, and may in some cases be associated with the River Dee (  compare  Clyde  )."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705182,"age":28,"year":"1066","julianDay":2110409,"title":"Battle of Hastings","description":"Battle of Hastings was fought between the Norman-French army and the battle-wary English army on October 14, 1066. Duke William of Normandy believed he was the rightful king rather than Harold, who had been crowned king several months earlier. Harold was killed in battle and William was crowned king on Christmas Day 1066.","url":"https://www.english-heritage.org.uk/learn/1066-and-the-norman-conquest/what-happened-battle-hastings/","urlTitle":"English Heritage - Battle of Hastings","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705183,"age":48,"year":"1086","julianDay":2117714,"title":"Domesday Book","description":"Domesday Book is Britain's earliest extant public record with information containing land surveys and landholdings commissioned by William I. The book was completed in 1086.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/domesday/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Domesday","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705184,"age":58,"year":"1096","julianDay":2121366,"title":"The Crusades","description":"A series of religious wars between Christians and Muslims, known as the Crusades, occurred between 1096 and 1291, and played a large role in European Christian dominance in the Middle East.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/middle-ages/crusades","urlTitle":"History - The Crusades","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Ernald I de Percy was born in 1038, in Kildale, Yorkshire, England, his father, Geoffrey de Percy Sieur, was 33 and his mother, Margaret, was 34. He married Mrs Ernald I de Percy before 1069, in Europe. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1096, in Hull, Yorkshire, England, at the age of 58."},"et":{"1038–1096":"1038–1096","–Female":"Surnud","1069–1140":"1069–1140","1005–Male":"1005–Surnud","1005–Female":"1005–Surnud","1038":"1038","before 1038":"enne 1038","1005":"1005","before 1069":"enne 1069","1069":"1069","1066":"1066","1086":"1086","1096":"1096","1140":"1140","Europe":"Europe","Stokesley, Yorkshire, England":"Stokesley, Yorkshire, England","Hull, Yorkshire, England":"Hull, Yorkshire, England","Kildale, Yorkshire, England":"Kildale, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"1038–1096":"1038–1096","–Female":"Kuollut","1069–1140":"1069–1140","1005–Male":"1005–Kuollut","1005–Female":"1005–Kuollut","1038":"1038","before 1038":"ennen vuotta 1038","1005":"1005","before 1069":"ennen vuotta 1069","1069":"1069","1066":"1066","1086":"1086","1096":"1096","1140":"1140","Europe":"Europe","Stokesley, Yorkshire, England":"Stokesley, Yorkshire, England","Hull, Yorkshire, England":"Hull, Yorkshire, England","Kildale, Yorkshire, England":"Kildale, Yorkshi